**Phase 1: If You Need to Lose Fat**
- Moderate calorie deficit (300-500 below maintenance)
- High protein (0.8-1g per lb bodyweight)
- Prioritize whole foods
- Don't crash diet—preserves muscle

**Phase 2: Building Muscle (Curves)**
- Slight surplus (100-200 calories above maintenance)
- High protein (1g per lb minimum)
- Carbs around workouts for performance
- This is where curves actually get built

**The Recomp Option:**
At maintenance calories with high protein:
- Lose fat while gaining muscle
- Slower but effective for beginners
- Less dramatic weight changes
- Body composition improves

**Protein Is Non-Negotiable:**
| Protein Intake | Outcome |
|----------------|---------|
| Under 0.5g/lb | Muscle loss, no curves |
| 0.5-0.7g/lb | Maintenance, slow progress |
| 0.8-1g/lb | Optimal for most |
| 1g+/lb | Aggressive building |

**Meal Timing (Simple Version):**
- Protein every meal
- Carbs around training
